        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-03-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="240" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d240">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Harvey</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 134.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-03-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 31, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi>Your despatch No. 264, of the 10th of March,
                    relative to the presence of the rebel cruiser Florida at Funchal, and her
                    departure thence on the 29th of last month, has been received. The course of
                    proceeding which you propose to adopt with regard to this matter is
                    approved.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James E. Harvey</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c.</hi>, &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., <hi rend="italic">Lisbon.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
